long_desc.thetext:
Its easy to reproduce the behavior with the following code:

var tree = new qx.ui.tree.Tree().set({
  width : 200,
  height : 400
});
this.getRoot().add(tree);

var root = new qx.ui.tree.TreeFolder("root");
root.setOpen(true);
tree.setRoot(root);

var te1_2 = new qx.ui.tree.TreeFolder("Workspace");
te1_2.setOpen(true);
root.add(te1_2);

var te1_2_1 = new qx.ui.tree.TreeFile("Windows (C:)");

// Funny behaviour:
te1_2_1.setModel('My model...');

var te1_2_2 = new qx.ui.tree.TreeFile("Documents (D:)");
te1_2.add(te1_2_1, te1_2_2);

â€‹
Just select the root and try to navigate the tree with the down key. The Selection is lost after it passes the tree item having its model property set.
